<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Afghan Taliban Arrest 2 Foreigners on Espionage Charges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Afghanistan's ruling Taliban
militia have arrested two foreigners on the charges of alleged
espionage in Kabul, Afghan sources said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The two foreigners, whose nationality and names were not
disclosed, were arrested in the Afghan capital a couple of days
ago with some documents that substantiated their involvement in
spying, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
They had recently arrived in Afghanistan. Further investigation
against the detainees are going on. The sources, however, did not
elaborate for whom they were spying.
</P>
<P>
Taliban in the past had arrested several Arab nationals for
their alleged involvement in spying against the Saudi dissident
Osama bin Laden, who is under the Islamic militia's protection
against the efforts by the United States to seize him. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
