<DOCNO> XIE20000418.0005 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mongolian, Vietnamese Presidents Meet for Closer Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Mongolian President Nachagyn
Bagabandi and his Vietnamese counterpart, Tran Duc Luong, agreed
here on Monday to strengthen cooperation in trade, economic,
scientific and technical areas between their two countries.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with Bagabandi, Luong said that it is
important for both countries to improve bilateral cooperation in
various sectors commensurate with the level of their present
political relations.
</P>
<P>
He suggested that the two sides should effectively use sea and
land transport through China's Tianjin port and the railway
linking the Vietnamese capital of Hanoi, Beijing and Ulan Bator.
</P>
<P>
"Vietnam is interested in setting up links between banks and
establishing cooperation among small- and medium-sized enterprises
in agricultural and other sectors" said Luong, who arrived here
Saturday for a three-day visit.
</P>
<P>
For his part, Bagabandi said Mongolia has paid great attention
to increasing cooperation with Vietnam in both international and
regional affairs. Developing relations with Asia-Pacific countries,
especially Vietnam, has taken an important place in Mongolia's
foreign policy, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Mongolian government decided in 1999 to try to increase
bilateral trade to 10 million U.S. dollars in the following five
years, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
