<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yugoslav Industrial Output Grows 112 Percent After War </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslavia's industrial
production in last month increased by 112 percent over that of
last May, when NATO ended air strikes against the country.
</P>
<P>
The industrial production of last month increased 8.5 percent
over February. The building material and non-metal sector
registered the highest growth rate of 34.6 percent, the Statistics
Bureau said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Despite high speed of economic growth during the past 10 months
after 78-day bombing of NATO, most industrial sectors have not
regained the production level before March, 1999, when the war
began, due to heavy losses in the bombing.
</P>
<P>
The industrial production in the first quarter of this year
decreased 5.3 percent over the same period of last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
