<DOCNO> XIE20000418.0007 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Increasing Bond Issue Not to Trigger off Inflation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 17 (Xinhua)-- Increasing bond issues will not
trigger off inflation, let alone cause a government debt crisis,
said Xiang Huaicheng, Chinese minister of finance here today.
</P>
<P>
Xiang, speaking at the ongoing China Business Summit 2000, said
that China's economy is developing on a healthy track in general
but there are still problems and contradictions resulting from
insufficient demand.
</P>
<P>
To drive domestic demand, China has decided to issue 100
billion yuan long-term bonds to support infrastructure
construction, technical upgrading in State-owned enterprises,
developing the western region, and education and science and
research projects, he explained.
</P>
<P>
Xiang said that the ratios of fiscal deficit and outstanding
bonds in the GDP stood at 2.8 percent and 12.7 percent
respectively last year, both within the safe limits as agreed
internationally.
</P>
<P>
He said that China is also strengthening study on preventing
financial crisis and are constantly improving on policy means to
maintain a safe financial situation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
