<DOCNO> XIE20000418.0008 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice Premier Meets Canadian Guests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Wen Jiabao
today met with Canadian Minister of Agriculture and Agri-food Lyle
Vanclief and his party.
</P>
<P>
Wen said that Sino-Canadian relations have witnessed steady
growth in political, economic, cultural and other areas since the
two countries formed their partnership of all-round cooperation
geared towards the 21st century in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Great potential remains to be tapped in the two countries'
agricultural cooperation, he said, adding that he hoped the two
sides would join efforts to enhance cooperation in agriculture.
</P>
<P>
Vanclief told Wen that Canada has some agricultural
technologies to share with China.
</P>
<P>
Vanclief and his party are here to attend the Seventh Session
of the China-Canada Joint Committee for Agricultural Cooperation
at the invitation of the Chinese Ministry of Agriculture.
</P>
</TEXT>
