<HEADLINE> Chinese President Arrives in Turkey for State Visit  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
arrived here Tuesday afternoon for a state visit to Turkey at the
invitation of his Turkish counterpart Suleyman Demirel.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Jiang will hold talks with Demirel and other
Turkish leaders on bilateral and international issues.
</P>
<P>
Jiang was greeted at the airport by Turkish State Minister Sukru
Sina Gerel, who will accompany Jiang on the visit all around, and
other high-ranking Turkish officials.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Ambassador to Turkey Yao Kuangyi and embassy staff were
present at the airport to welcome Jiang and his wife Wang Yeping.
</P>
<P>
In a written statement issued at the airport, Jiang said that
his visit to Turkey, which comes at the turn of the century, aims
to deepen mutual understanding, promote friendship and advance
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The visit also aims to establish a new cooperative partnership
between the two countries in the new era, for the benefit of the
two countries and the two peoples, he said.
</P>
<P>
"I look forward to holding constructive and fruitful talks with
President Suleyman Demirel and other Turkish leaders so as to make
joint efforts to achieve this goal," said Jiang.
</P>
<P>
He recalled that the friendship between the two peoples dates
back to 2,000 years ago, when their ancestors began friendly
contacts via the famous "Silk Road."
</P>
<P>
Since the establishment of diplomatic relations in 1971, Sino-
Turkish friendly exchanges in various fields increased and
cooperative relationship progressed, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese president said he was very pleased to pay a state
visit to Turkey, a renowned nation with ancient civilization, and
he had brought with him deep affections and good wishes from the
Chinese people to the friendly Turkish people.
</P>
<P>
Demirel is to hold a grand welcoming ceremony in honor of Jiang
at the Presidential Palace Wednesday morning.
</P>
<P>
Jiang's entourage arriving on the same special plane includes
Vice Premier Qian Qichen and his wife, State Councillor Wu Yi,
Director of the General Office of the Chinese Communist Party (CPC)
Central Committee Wang Gang, Minister in charge of the State
Development Planning Commission Zeng Peiyan, Director of the Policy
Research Office of CPC Central Committee Teng Wensheng, Vice
Foreign Minister Ji Peiding, Vice Director of the General Office of
the CPC Central Committee and Director of the Central Guards Bureau
You Xigui, Vice Minister of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation
Sun Guangxiang, Special Assistant Wang Huning and Director of
President Jiang's office Jia Ting'an.
</P>
<P>
Turkey is the third leg of Jiang's five-nation tour of Asia,
Europe and Africa, which has already taken him to Israel and
Palestine. Jiang flew to Egypt's Mediterranean port city of
Alexandria Monday for a meeting with President Hosni Mubarak.
</P>
<P>
Jiang will also visit Greece and South Africa before winding up
his three-continent tour. 
</P>
</TEXT>
