<HEADLINE> Romania Discovers Largest Gold Deposits in Europe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The geological and exploration
studies performed in Rosia Montana-Bucium area of western Romania
made obvious the existence of some resources of eight million gold
ounces, the largest gold deposits ever discovered in Europe, the
Gabriel Resources Ltd. Company's president Frank Timis announced
here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Drilling-exploration studies in Rosia Montana-Bucium area were
performed by Rosia Montana Gold Corporation joint venture and were
worth 20 million U.S. dollars. They were followed by a re-
feasibility study achieved by an American company.
</P>
<P>
According to the National Agency for Mineral Resources'
president Mihail Ianas, the feasibility study has to be concluded
until the end of the year. If it is going to be a positive one,
the project for the exploitation of the deposits must be prepared
in 2001.
</P>
<P>
"If the project receives the okay from the government, the
construction will start in 2001 and the production will start in 2-
3 years", Ianas said, adding that the investment would be a huge
one,worth over 250 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
For Romania's government, this investment is very important not
only because it might bring 200 million U.S. dollars but also for
the fact it will eliminate the subsidies and will create new jobs,
according to the Trade and Industry Ministry's state secretary Ion
Roman.
</P>
<P>
The implementation of this project in Rosia Montana area
requires the construction of all facilities of a modern
infrastructure at the standards imposed by the EU and the World
Bank. 
</P>
</TEXT>
