<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Draws Up New Financial Assistance Programs for Romania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) has
drawn up recently two new financial assistance programs for
Romania and nine other candidate countries, the official Rompres
news agency Tuesday quoted the EU representative here as saying.
</P>
<P>
One of these is the ISPA program worth one billion euros for
pre-accession structural policies. Romania will benefit up to 26
percent of the available funds to be used for transport and the
environment.
</P>
<P>
According to EU statistics, it will take Romania between 11 and
17 billion euros to upgrade its transport infrastructure to EU
standards and 20 billion euros to bring the environment in line
with EU regulations. EU will contribute about 75 percent of the
program costs for these fields, while the remaining will be borne
by Romania.
</P>
<P>
Prioritized under the ISPA program will be the finalization of
three European transport corridors to link Romania with the
Western countries. This year, two road rehabilitation and up-
grading projects as well as a railway project are proposed to be
unfolded.
</P>
<P>
They will concern the Bucharest-Giurgiu road, the Bucharest-
Constanta road and the railway road from Bucharest to Giurgiu.
Upgrading works on the Craiova-Lugoj-Timisoara road as well as
construction works on belt roads around Pitesti, Sebes, Deva,Alba
Iulia and Sibiu are also planned to be performed under the same
program next year.
</P>
<P>
Three priorities under the ISPA environmental headings will be
water supply, air pollution and waste treatment.
</P>
<P>
The second program - SAPARD, worth 500 million euros, will be
aimed at agriculture and rural development. Romania is planned to
receive 30 percent of the amount.
</P>
<P>
European financiers have identified four field all concerning
the private farming sector, among which the development of private
farms and farm processing units and agro-tourism. In order to
ensure a viable character of the projects under this program,
important funds will be allotted for the improvement of rural
telecommunications, power and water supply as PHARE program stands
at 240 million euros. All the funds will be used for the
harmonization of Romanian legislature with the European one, the
intaking of the EU aquis communautaire, as well as for regional
development and infrastructure investment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
