violence in the run-up to parliamentary elections with many people
having been beaten for supporting an opposing party.
</P>
<P>
Two members of the Movement for Democratic Change were torched
to death last Saturday after petrol bombs were hurled into their
car.
</P>
<P>
Two white commercial farmers were shot dead allegedly by war
veterans who abducted them following the clashes between their
workers and ex- combatants occupying their farms. 
