<HEADLINE> Merrymaking Festival on Southern China Island Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua)-- South China's Hainan Province is
going to sponsor its first ever "China Hainan Merrymaking Festival
" on November 3-24, as another act of PR to promote itself as one
of the world's tourism destinations.
</P>
<P>
During the festival, marriage ceremonies will be held in
addition to sailboat racing, sand beach volleyball contests,
dragon boat race and forest tourism. Some seminars on island
tourism and related policies will also be held during the festival.
</P>
<P>
Hainan vice governor Li Dongsheng made the announcement at a
press conference here today. He said that the festival will be a
showcase for the world of the island province's colorful and rich
tourism resources and beautiful natural ecology.
</P>
<P>
He hoped that winter will be Hainan's tourism peak season.
</P>
<P>
Slightly smaller than Taiwan, Hainan, once a part of the
Guangdong Province, was upgraded to an separate province in 1988.
Last year, the province received over 9.2 million tourists and the
revenue from tourism accounted for 15.4 percent of the provincial
GDP.
</P>
<P>
The province has over 500 hotels and resorts, 184 travel
agencies. Two airports on the island, in addition to highway
networks and around-the-island expressway, make the island easily
accessible.  
</P>
</TEXT>
