<HEADLINE> PLA's Research Group Praised For Anti-Malaria Medicine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- A research group from a Medical
Research Institute attached to the Chinese People's Liberation
Army (PLA) has been praised today at a meeting held by the PLA
General Logistics Department for their contributions to
developing new anti-malaria medicine.
</P>
<P>
The new medicine, which has a success rate of 95 percent
against malignant malaria, is China's first chemically composed
medicine and has successfully entered the markets of western
developed countries.
</P>
<P>
Wang Ke, a members of the Central Military Commission and head
of the PLA General Logistics Department, said in his speech that
the PLA should firmly carry out "invigorating logistics work
through science and technology."
</P>
<P>
Malaria, one of the top ten infectious diseases in the world,
particularly strikes soldiers conducting military training in
tropical areas. Currently the disease attacks more than 500
million people and kills two million a year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
