<HEADLINE> Karachi Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KARACHI, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Bulls kept on dominating the
Karachi stock market Tuesday, pouring 26.62 points, or 1.35
percent, to the 100-share index which closed at 2,002.33.
</P>
<P>
The market on Monday opened with a bearish tint, but
finished with a marginal bullish tone in the evening, paving the
way for strong opening Tuesday morning.
</P>
<P>
The morning sentiment was well kept through the day and
strengthened the market with market capital soaring to 506.58
billion rupees (9.74 billion U.S. dollars) from 499.83 billion
rupees (9.61 billion dollars) of the previous day,dealers said.
</P>
<P>
The turnover also increased from 224.65 million shares of the
previous day to Tuesday's 296.80 million shares.
</P>
