<HEADLINE> British Foreign Secretary Visits Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bangkok, April 18 (Xinhua) -- British Foreign Secretary Robin
Cook arrived here Tuesday night to start the second leg of his
three-nation Asian tour, Thai Foreign Ministry sources said.
</P>
<P>
Cook will hold talks with Thai Prime Minister Chuan Leekpai and
his Thai counterpart Surin Pitsuwan separately on Wednesday
morning.
</P>
<P>
A news conference is scheduled after the talks.
</P>
<P>
Cook will leave Thailand and fly to Nepal on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Cook started his Asian trip on April 15, with India as his
first stop, followed by Thailand and Nepal. 
</P>
