<HEADLINE> Russia Starts Strategic Aviation Maneuvers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The Russian Air Force started
tactical training in its long-range (strategic) aviation on
Tuesday, the Interfax news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The five-day maneuver, which involves Tu-160, Tu95MS and Tu-22
MZ strategic bombers, Su-27 and MiG-29 frontline airplanes and A-
50 radar and detection aircraft, will be conducted over the Middle
and Low Volga lands and above the Black and Caspian seas, the Air
Force headquarters said.
</P>
<P>
"It is the first time since the collapse of the USSR that Tu-
160 strategic bombers will fly over the Black Sea," Interfax
quoted the Russian military as saying.
</P>
<P>
A total of 40 sorties will be conducted within the framework
of the training, Interfax said. 
</P>
