<HEADLINE> China, Canada Form JV on Green Vegetable Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- A multi-million dollar China-
Canada joint venture on green vegetable production has officially
started business in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Visiting Canadian Minister of Agricultural and Agri-food Lyle
Vanclief and Canadian Ambassador to China Howard Balloch attended
the ribbon-cutting ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Beijing Shunxin Agricultural Holding Co., the Chinese investor,
holds 52 percent of the 3.6 million U.S. dollars investment, while
Canadian Hydronov Co., the world's leading lettuce producer, held
the remaining 48 percent.
</P>
<P>
A computerized production line will monitor the whole vegetable
production process from seedlings to packaging. This production
line is widely used in Canada, U.S. and Beijing and Shenzhen.
</P>
<P>
The new company has already built a greenhouse with a total
area of 14,000 square meters and a 1,000-square-meter processing
and packaging workshop. The daily production capacity is set to
reach 10,000 lettuces after full operation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
