<HEADLINE> 500 kg of Drugs Seized by China's Custom Offices in 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Custom Offices cracked
over 150 drug cases, confiscating more than 500 kg of drugs in
1999, an official from the National Narcotic Control Commission
said today.
</P>
<P>
He said that custom officers cracked 13 major cases,
confiscating approximately 400 kg of drugs, or some 78 percent of
the total.
</P>
<P>
Besides, custom offices across China seized more than 20 tons
of chemical products used for making drugs, 22 tons of poppyseed
as well as more than nine million psychedelic tablets.
</P>
<P>
Custom officers also cracked 42 drug-related mail cases,
involving some 16 kg of drugs.
</P>
<P>
China's narcotics situation is getting worse. In 1999, there
were 680,000 drug addicts, 14.3 percent more than in 1998.
</P>
<P>
Among China's drug addicts, eighty percent are male. Seventy-
eight percent are aged between 17 and 35. More than 490,000
addicts take heroin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
