<HEADLINE> 2,000 Illegally Captured Wild Birds Released </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, April 18 (Xinhua) -- More than 2,000 illegally
captured wild birds were released today in Qilihai, Ninghe County
of north China's Tianjin Municipality, at the start of the 15th "
Love Bird Week" in Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
As the largest port city in north China, Tianjin is an
important habitat for many Asian migrant birds. Qilihai, a nature
reserve approved by the State Council in 1992, is a resting place
for more than 100 kinds of birds, of which a dozen of them are
rare birds.
</P>
<P>
In an effort to protect the environment and the birds, the
Tianjin Municipal government today urged police forces to enhance
efforts to deal with illegal bird hunters and called on municipal
legislators to work out more laws and regulations to protect birds.
</P>
</TEXT>
