<HEADLINE> China Spring Commodity Fair Opens in Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The five-day China Spring
Commodity Fair opened today in north China's Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
According to organizers, over 3,000 enterprises from 26
provinces, municipalities, and autonomous regions will display
their products including garments, decorations and household
electrical appliances.
</P>
<P>
Enterprises and delegations from five western provinces,
including Guizhou, Yunnan, Gansu, Tibet and Shaanxi, are attending
the Fair. Gansu also plans to hold a press conference and trade
negotiations during the event to attract more investment.
</P>
<P>
Lectures on China's entry into the World Trade Organization
will be held and strategies for developing China's western regions
will also be discussed at the Fair, said organizers.
</P>
<P>
The Fair is one of the two important domestic commodity fairs in
the country. The trade value for the previous six Fairs totaled 45.
5 billion yuan (5.46 billion U.S. dollars).
