<HEADLINE> Large Hydrocarbon Resin Plant Goes into Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 18 (Xinhua) -- China's largest hydrocarbon
resin enterprise, involving a total investment of 29 million US
dollars, went into operation today.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Jinsen Hydrocarbon Resins Co. Ltd. was jointly
established by the U.S. Exxonmobil Chemical consortium, and
Shanghai Oil and Chemicals Corporation Ltd..
</P>
<P>
Exxonmobil Chemical holds 60 percent of the shares of the joint
venture, and the Shanghai corporation holds 40 percent, local
sources said.
</P>
<P>
The venture will use state-of-the-art technology to turn out
chemical products needed by China and other Asian-Pacific regions,
said authorities.
</P>
<P>
Exxonmobil Chemical has a sales network in more than 60
countries, while Shanghai Oil and Chemicals Corporation Ltd. is
one of the largest oil and chemical enterprise in China.
</P>
