<HEADLINE> Newspaper Article Stresses Guarding Against Nuclear War in 21st Century </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- China should not give up its
efforts to prevent nuclear war as it prepares against potential
military conflict, since the specter of nuclear conflict will
continue to loom over mankind in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
So said Dong Qingfu at a just-concluded seminar on military
science, predicting that in the coming century nuclear weapons
will play an indispensable and important role in international
affairs, the People's Liberation Army Daily reported today.
</P>
<P>
He said the struggle centered on the issue of nuclear weapons
may become more complicated and fierce while the shadow of nuclear
war, particularly limited ones, will remain.
</P>
<P>
"Basically, China's nuclear strategy is one that opposes wars
and safeguards peace," he said.
</P>
<P>
"China has adopted a very prudent and restrained attitude
toward nuclear weapons testing and nuclear arsenal buildups," he
said.
</P>
<P>
China was the first country in the world to announce that it
would not be the first to use nuclear weapons, Dong said.
</P>
