<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, chairman of the
Standing Committee of the National People's Congress, has urged to
develop China's market economy, improve democracy and the legal
system in the country.
</P>
<P>
The top lawmaker, who is also a member of the Standing
Committee of the Political Bureau of the Communist Party of China
Central Committee, made the call during his inspection tour of
central Henan Province from April 13-17. He visited Zhengzhou, the
provincial capital, and Luoyang and Kaifeng with provincial
leaders.
</P>
<P>
During his stay, Li paid great attention to the work of local
legislatures. Local people's congresses and local laws and
regulations are playing a big role in promoting local development,
he said.
</P>
<P>
Li said the role of local legislators is extremely important,
noting that over 3.2 million local lawmakers are representatives
of people of different trades.
</P>
<P>
Li asked local legislators to increase their contacts with
ordinary people and urged standing committees of local people's
congresses to create good conditions for lawmakers to carry out
their work.
</P>
<P>
On April 17, Li visited the Xiaolangdi Water Control Project on
the Yellow River, 40 km north of Luoyang, to learn about current
developments in the multi-billion yuan project.
</P>
<P>
During his talks with local leaders, Li praised Henan for its
progress in family-planning, farming, tourism and development of
science and technology. He also urged local officials to make all
efforts to curb corruption.  
</P>
