<HEADLINE> Sharif's Appeal Admitted by High Court </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sources from Karachi, provincial capital of Sindh, told Xinhua
that a division bench of the high court accepted the appeal after
listening to arguments of the lawyers from both the prosecution
and Sharif.
</P>
<P>
The court also set May 2 for hearing of another appeal filed by
the ousted prime minister against confiscation of his property,
according to the sources.
</P>
<P>
The petition challenging the ATC verdict of awarding life
sentence to Sharif had earlier been filed by a lawyer Azizullah
Sheikh on behalf of the former prime minister, who was deposed on
October 12, last year in a bloodless coup.
</P>
