evidence of the prosecution about six other accused was not
accepted but the seventh was sentenced.
</P>
<P>
On April 6, Nawaz Sharif was sentenced to life imprisonment on
two courts, fine of 100 million rupees (1.9 million U.S.dollars)
and 200 million rupees (3.9 million dollars) as compensation
besides confiscation of property.
</P>
<P>
The former prime minister, along with other six, had been
charged with refusing landing in Karachi of a civil plane which
carried back from abroad some 200 passengers including the now
chief executive General Pervez Musharraf on October 12, 1999.
