<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 4 People Killed in Train Accident in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 18 (Xinhua) -- At least four people were killed
and eight others seriously injured when three trains collided
early Tuesday at a village in Karawang regency, Indonesia's West
Java Province, a report reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
The accident involved three trains -- the Jakarta-bound Argo
Bromo executive train, a freight train carrying steel and cattle
and a Bandung-bound freight train carrying containers," the
Antara News Agency quoted Spokesman of the state-owned railway
company Gatot Wibowoyang as saying.
</P>
<P>
"The accident occurred when the Bandung train smashed into the
tail of the freight train, derailing most of their carriages,"
Wibowoyang said, adding that the accident took place when the
Bandung-bound freight trains operators failed to heed railway
signals.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the Argo Bromo executive train, which came
from the opposite direction, failed to avoid the accident,
derailing two of its wagons, he said.
</P>
<P>
The accident has led to the cancellation of all trips to and
from northern Java territories. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
