held on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
On the same day, defendant lawyers filed an appeal against the
life sentence awarded to the ousted prime minister.
</P>
<P>
Nawaz Sharif was sentenced to life imprisonment, fine of one
million rupees (1.9 million U.S. dollars) and 2 million rupees (3.
8 million dollars) as compensation besides confiscation of his
property on April 6.
</P>
<P>
He, along with other six, was charged with refusing the landing
at Karachi airport of a civil plane which carried back from abroad
some 200 passengers including the current Chief Executive General
Pervez Musharraf on October 12 last year. 
