dive to a new 18-month low below 59 U.S. cents Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The currency dropped around one U.S. cent overnight and reached
its lowest level since October 1998 when it was climbing back
after the Asian economic crisis.
</P>
<P>
It closed at 59.37 U.S. cents from 60.31 Monday.
</P>
<P>
At 17:00 Australian East time, the Australian dollar was at 0.
6255 euro from 0.6245.
</P>
<P>
Economists said Tuesday that the Australian dollar was looking
increasingly sick and could fall dramatically further before
finding a platform for a slow recovery. They believed an increase
in the Australia/U.S. interest rate differential is bearish for
the currency because it lures investors from Australian dollar
bonds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
