<HEADLINE> Australian One Nation Party Faces New Trouble </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The notorious One Nation Party
of Australia is threatened to be deregistrated in The New South
Wales state Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The party has been charged with over-reporting its membership
number in order to lodge its registration application in the 1998
general election.
</P>
<P>
According to a report by Australian Associated Press, the state
's electoral Commissioner John Wasson said Tuesday the One Nation
Party had so far failed to provide sufficient evidence of the bona
fides of its membership.
</P>
<P>
The One Nation Party arose in 1997 as a racialist-colour party
and won a glorious victory in the 1998 election. 
</P>
