<HEADLINE> Agassi Given Chance to Win Two Sports Awards  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Ameircan tennis legend Andre
Agassi has been given a thoretical chance to win two sports awards
when he was announced as nominee for world sportsman of the year
and world comback of the year.
</P>
<P>
In a press conference for the inaugural Laureus Sports Awards,
Agassi, sprinter Maurice Greene and golfer Tiger Woods were
announced as nominees for world sportsman of the year.
</P>
<P>
Other nominees announced Tuesday include American tennis player
Lindsay Davenport, American sprinter Marion Jones and Romanian
athlete Gabriela Szabo for world sportswoman of the year;
Australian rugby union team, Manchester United football team and
United States women's football team for world team of the year;
Americans Tony Hawk, Shaun Palmer and Travis Pastrana for world
alternative sportsperson of the year; Brian Frasure, Beatrice Hess
and Louise Sauvage for world sportsperson of the year with
disability; Agassi,Lance Armstrong and Ludmilla Engqvist for world
comback of the year;and Sergio Garcio, Kurt Warner and Serena
Williams for world newcomer of the year.
</P>
<P>
The Laureus Sports Awards, the first annual ceremony to
celebrate sports excellence across all disciplines and all
continents, will honour sporting achievement in an annual TV
entertainment spectacular in the same way that the Academy Awards
recognise outstanding performance in the film industry.
</P>
<P>
Nominations for the awards were submitted by more than 230
sports journalists in more than 75 countries worldwide and the
winner will be announced in a ceremony in Monte Carlo, Monaco on
May 25th. Each winner will receive a Laureus statuette, named
after the Latin word for Laurel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
