<HEADLINE> Tianjin External Trade Surges in 1st Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The external trade value of north
China's Tianjin Municipality surged 37.7 percent in the first
quarter this year to 3.716 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The import value of the city reached 1.762 billion U.S. dollars,
a rise of 46.2 percent over the same period last year, while
export value was 1.955 billion U.S. dollars, rising 30.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
The exports of various enterprises in the city also were on the
increase in the first three months, as the export value of foreign-
funded enterprises was 1.371 billion U.S. dollars, rising 27.8
percent, and the export value of state-owned enterprises
registered a rise of 40.4 percent to reach 549 million U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin's exports to Asia, Europe, and North America rose 30.6,
35.6 and 32.7 percent, respectively, for the period.
</P>
<P>
As one of largest open cities in China, Tianjin is a prime
economic centers of north China, and the surge of its external
trade value in the first quarter reflects the economic recovery in
Asia, according to economic observers.
</P>
<P>
Many experts expect that the city's exports will exceed 7
billion U.S. dollars this year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
