<HEADLINE> Economic Official on Further Opening up of Central and Western China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Yu Xiaosong, chairman of the
China Council for the Promotion of International Trade, urged
western and central China to further promote opening to the
outside world.
</P>
<P>
At the 2000 Henan Economic and Trade Fair, which is being
hosted in this capital of central China's Henan Province, Yu said
he has confidence in the region's development prospects based on
its experience of reform and opening up over the past twenty years.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the region should follow the example of the
country's coastal regions, especially Guangdong and Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
As part of the implementation of the national strategy of
developing central and western China, the provinces of Sichuan,
Shaanxi, and Henan have hosted a series of economic and trade
exchange activities this year, signing agreements for cooperative
projects with overseas investors valued at billions of US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Yu suggested that local governments in the region establish
long-term relationships with overseas investors and carry out
investment fairs worldwide.
</P>
<P>
Domestic investment and interprovincial cooperation will also
play an important role in developing the economy of the region,
the official said.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, central and western China must make great
effort to train and introduce outstanding professionals from
around the world to meet the needs of opening up and development,
he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
