<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Rural Areas Recognize Importance of IT </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Internet, the fastest means for
people to exchange information in today's world, has been warmly
welcomed in China's rural areas now.
</P>
<P>
A poor county named Jingyu in northeast China's Jilin Province
has been able to get useful economic information through the hi-
tech medium.
</P>
<P>
Located in the Changbai Mountains, the county now still has no
highways or railway lines connecting the outside world. It will
take villagers some two hours to arrive in the nearest Baishan
City by bus. And it is almost impossible for local people to read
any intraday newspapers.
</P>
<P>
"Capital, technology, and talents are important for our
economic development, but communication and exchange of
information with the outside world is on the top of these," said
Ji Deping, secretary of the county committee of the Communist
Party of China.
</P>
<P>
Outsiders can also get information about the county's resources,
investment projects and tourism routes through Internet. And some
businessmen from other provinces and from Singapore and Hong Kong
have already shown their interest and willingness to participate
in the local economic development.
</P>
<P>
Internet has also brought opportunities and fortune to the
farmers and livestock breeders in north China's Inner Mongolia
Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
Bai Yelha, owner of a lamb processing factory in Chen Barag
Banner, has begun to gain profits for the first time in the last
two years by signing a long-term product supply contract online
with a restaurant in northeast China's Heilongjiang province.
</P>
<P>
The factory had been running at loss before this due to lack of
market information. It is Internet that helps him solve the
problem, he said.
</P>
<P>
"Trade negotiations by going on business trips will cost a lot
of money and time, while Internet chatrooms have made all trade
negotiations economical, convenient and prompt," said Ms. Song, a
managing staff with a local cashmere company.
</P>
<P>
Internet has expanded the business scope as well. The Shiqi
Group, a clothing company based in the region, now make suits and
dresses for foreigners according to the orders they sent through
Internet.
</P>
<P>
More enterprises and livestock breeders in the region are now
realizing the great help of such a hi-tech means, and so far, over
20 companies have opened Internet sales business.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
