<HEADLINE> China Issues Treasury Bonds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- China issued 28 billion yuan (3.
37 billion U.S. dollars) worth of treasury bonds on Monday.
</P>
<P>
This is the second batch of registered treasury bonds that
China issued this year. The T-bonds have floating interest rates
and a maturity term of ten years.
</P>
<P>
Thirty Chinese financial institutions have underwritten the
issuance of these T-bonds, including the Industrial and Commercial
Bank of China and Construction Bank of China.
</P>
<P>
China issued 20 billion yuan worth of registered treasury bonds
in February with a maturity term of seven years. 
