<HEADLINE> Facts &AMP; Figures: Mortality of Chinese in 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Following are detailed figures of
the mortality rate of the Chinese people in 1999, provided by the
Ministry of Health:
</P>
<P>
Total in Cities: 5.88 per 1,000 people;
</P>
<P>
Urban Male:  6.35 per 1,000 people;
</P>
<P>
Urban Female:  5.39 per 1,000 people;
</P>
<P>
Big Cities:  6.21 per 1,000 people;
</P>
<P>
Small &AMP; Medium-sized Cities: 4.70 per 1,000 people;
</P>
<P>
Total in Rural Areas:  6.06 per 1,000 people;
</P>
<P>
Rural Male:  6.60 per 1,000 people;
</P>
<P>
Rural Female:  5.51 per 1,000 people;
</P>
<P>
Developed Rural Areas: 6.36 per 1,000 people;
</P>
<P>
Underdeveloped Areas:  5.79 per 1,000 people.
</P>
<P>
Proportions of death tolls in different age groups are as the
following:
</P>
<P>
1) Urban Area
</P>
<P>
Under 5:  1.25 percent;
</P>
<P>
5-19 Age Group:  0.92 percent;
</P>
<P>
20-64 Age Group: 28.68 percent;
</P>
<P>
65 and Above:  69.15 percent;
</P>
<P>
2) Rural Area
</P>
<P>
Under 5:  3.92 percent;
</P>
<P>
5-19 Age Group:  1.91 percent;
</P>
<P>
20-64 Age Group: 33.42 percent;
</P>
<P>
65 and Above:  60.75 percent.  
</P>
