<HEADLINE> Insurancestreet.net Goes Live to Provide On-line Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Insurancestreet.net, the one-
stop insurance portal from SUNeVision, will go live Wednesday with
23 insurance companies offering products directly to consumers.
</P>
<P>
With insurancestreet.net, consumers can use the Internet to
access information on a full range of products offered by 23 major
insurance companies.
</P>
<P>
Insurance products on offer include medical, home contents,
fire, domestic helper, travel, personal injury and motor vehicle
coverage, as well as hospital cash, golf, and clinic package
insurance.
</P>
<P>
Insurancestreet.net is the latest of a planned series of
Superstreet Internet portal for consumers, following the launch of
propertystreet.net, said Herbert HUI, Managing Director of
SUNevision, the technology and infrastructure and e-business
flagship of Sun Hung Kai Properties (SHKP).
</P>
<P>
The next portal will be Bankingstreet.net, which is in the
final stage of preparation and will go on-line by the end of this
month, according to Herbert HUI. 
</P>
</TEXT>
