<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Builds Ecological Demonstration Zones </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, April 18 (Xinhua) -- China, worrying about a
worsening environment, will take effective measures to turn 140 of
its 2,000 counties and prefectures into ecological demonstration
zones over the next five years.
</P>
<P>
These counties and prefectures are to meet the economic, social,
and environmental requirements of China's sustainable development
strategy in 2005.
</P>
<P>
An official with China's State Environmental Protection
Administration (SEPA) said the move is part of the country's
endeavor to achieve a fast economic growth while maintaining a
sound environment.
</P>
<P>
China began to construct ecological demonstration zones in 1995,
and by the end of last year, 33 counties and prefectures across
the country have been named as ecological demonstration zones by
SEPA.
</P>
<P>
The environmental requirements contain 19 specific development
targets, including the forest coverage rate, the consumption rate
of environment-friendly energy, and reduction in consumption of
farm chemicals and chemical fertilizers, as well as the quality of
air and water and the use of recycled solid waste.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
