<DOCNO> XIE20000418.0197 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: Major Zones in Pudong (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Waigaoqiao Bonded Zone, which lies in the northeastern part
of Pudong, covers an area of 10 square meters. It is a
comprehensive free trade zone with bonded warehouses, commodity
exhibition stands, trade fairs and export processing centers.
Intel, Hewlett-Packard and several other big names have
established plants in the area. By the end of last year, 3,975
projects have been approved within the area, involving a total
investment of 4.8 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Zhangjiang High-tech Park is located in the central part of
Pudong covering an area of 25 square kilometers. By the end of
1999, investors from both home and abroad have set up 67 projects,
mostly high-tech, with investment exceeding one billion US dollars.
Since July 1999, a one-square-kilometer area was set aside for
intensive development of new technologies, such as information,
biology, microelectronics and computer software.
</P>
<P>
On top of the four, Pudong also has other functional areas like
Sunqiao Modern Agriculture Development Zone, Huaxia Culture
Tourism Zone, Wangqiao Industrial Zone, and Liuli Modern
Residential Quarters. Establishment of various zones have promoted
Pudong's economy and at the same time spurred the development of
its surrounding areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
