<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Opposed to National Separatism, Interference: Spokesman  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- China treasures friendly
relations with neighboring countries, and allows no interference
into its internal affairs by any country in the name of ethnic
affairs or religion, said Foreign Ministry spokesman Sun Yuxi at a
press conference today.
</P>
<P>
In response to a question on President Jiang Zemin's upcoming
visit to Turkey and on exiled Uygur (ethnic group) separatists
based in the central-Asia region, Sun said that China attaches
great importance to unity, equality and common development between
different ethnic groups in the country, and strongly opposes
national separatism in any form.
</P>
<P>
National separatism "has played a negative role in national and
regional stability," Sun pointed out, saying that the Chinese
government has kept close watch on the situation and has expounded
its position on this matter to relevant countries.
</P>
<P>
"We believe that the countries concerned agree with China on
its opposition to all forms of national separatism," Sun said.
</P>
</TEXT>
