<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Manila Pledges to Address Concerns of Lanao Evacuees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine government vowed
Tuesday to assist residents of the southern province of Lanao
affected by clashes between government soldiers and members of the
Moro Islamic Liberation Front (MILF).
</P>
<P>
Defense Secretary Orlando Mercado said in a press statement
that the National Disaster Coordinating Council (NDCC) has set up
26 evacuation centers in both North and South Lanao provinces in
the Mindanao area.
</P>
<P>
"We set up 14 centers in North Lanao and 12 in South Lanao.
This is in line with President Estrada's order to extend
assistance to them,"Mercado said.
</P>
<P>
Several thousand of residents in some areas in the two
provinces have been reportedly forced to evacuate their homes
following recent fighting between government troops and the MILF
rebels.
</P>
<P>
Mercado said that as NDCC chairman, he has coordinated with the
National Food Authority to provide food for the evacuees. He said
the food supply for evacuees remain sufficient.
</P>
<P>
"We continue to coordinate with the Health Department and the
local government units. So far we allow the evacuees to go home
once the area is clear and safe to return to," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
