<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ECOWAS to Finalize Plan on Fast-Track Integration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The fast-track approach toward West
African integration took a leap Monday when a regional technical
committee started finalizing an integration blueprint for adoption
by the region's leaders in Ghana's capital Accra.
</P>
<P>
About 200 dignitaries form the Economic Community of West
African States (ECOWAS) will attend a mini-summit to adopt the
plan, said Kwamena Ahwoi, Ghana's Minister of Regional Economic
Integration and Cooperation, in Accra on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The mini-summit will be the second of this kind after last one
held on March 27 this year in Abuja, Nigeria's capital.
</P>
<P>
The fast-tracking, which was initiated by Ghana and Nigeria,
covers the creation of a second monetary zone among Ghana, Gambia,
Sierra Leone, Nigeria, Guinea and Liberia, and the free movement
of goods, services and people in these countries.
</P>
<P>
It also covers such regional infrastructure projects as a rail
line between Accra and Lagos and the promotion of private sector
mutual investment.
</P>
<P>
The second monetary zone would later be fused with the African
Financial Community (CFA) Franc to achieve the objective of the
ECOWAS, Ahwoi said.
</P>
<P>
ECOWAS has targeted 2004 as the year to achieve a single
convertible regional currency in area with a population of about
250 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000418.0210 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambian River Faces Worsening Weed Problem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The Kafue River weed problem has
continued to deteriorate despite combined efforts by the Zambian
government and various environment bodies to control the water
hyacinth.
</P>
<P>
The Zambia Daily Mail newspaper Tuesday quoted Environmental
Council of Zambia (ECZ) as warning that if no tangible measures
are worked out soon, developmental projects including
infrastructure on the banks of the river and living creatures
around it will face extinction in the very near future.
</P>
<P>
Without proper control measures, the hyacinth may adversely
affect some operations of the companies including Zambia
Electricity Supply Corporation (ZESCO), Zambia Sugar PLC and
Zambia Railways, ECZ said.
</P>
<P>
The major problem ZESCO is facing is the encroachment of the
weed on its turbines from which the power supplied to many parts
of the country and Lusaka in particular, is generated.
</P>
<P>
The spread of the weed will also lower the water level and make
 impassable the Kafue River, one of the three major branches of
the Zambezi River or the fourth longest river in Africa.
</P>
<P>
The weed has also affected activities including fishing, the
lifeline for some communities living on the river banks.
</P>
<P>
Aquatic Weed and algae Eradication Control Services (AWAECS)
has promised to jointly coordinate the prevention of the spread of
the weed with ECZ.
</P>
<P>
AWAECS will help eradicate the weed by chemical control
systems, using a special herbicide, which has been tested and
proved to be safe for both water and human life and has been used
in many countries for over 40 years now, according to AWAECS
project manager Chambika kamupila. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000418.0211 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Vs China Soccer Match to Be Held in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese national soccer
team will play against the Hong Kong team in a match scheduled for
April 25 at the Hong Kong Stadium, the Hong Kong Footaball
Association announced Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The match, named "Chinadotcom Corporation Challenge", was
sponsored by pan-Asian internet company Chinadotcom Corporation to
offer an opportunity for the two teams to learn from each other.
</P>
<P>
In China's squad there will be top Chinese talents striker Li
Wei Feng and midfielder Li Jinyu.
</P>
<P>
In the past 30 years since records, Hong Kong and China have
played a total of 14 matches, with 8 won by China, 3 by Hong Kong
and 3 matches drawn.
</P>
<P>
The challenge match will be broadcast live on the hongkong.com
portal in an exclusive first-ever live Webcast of a football match
in Hong Kong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
