<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tajima Sets National Swimming Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Yasuko Tajima beat her own national
record to win the women's 400 meters individual medley at the
Japanese national swimming championships on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Tajima, 18, clocked four minutes 39.13 seconds, beating her
previous mark of 4:39.45 set at the 1998 World Championships in
Perth.
</P>
<P>
This was her fourth straight national title in the event.
</P>
</TEXT>
