<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Germany's Allianz to Increase Presence in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Germany's Allianz, a major
global insurance provider, is considering cooperating with Chinese
insurers in promoting liability insurance in China.
</P>
<P>
Reinhard Schwarz of Allianz's Global Risk Division said here
recently that although China has just initiated liability
insurance, it has great potential in this area as the economy
maintains a high growth.
</P>
<P>
Schwarz predicted that liability insurance will develop most
rapidly in such industries as information technology, food, and
genetic engineering in China because these industries not only
bring about undoubted benefits but also pose huge potential risks.
</P>
<P>
Schwarz said that Allianz is especially willing to provide
liability insurance services to large Chinese manufacturers.
</P>
<P>
Allianz began its business in China in 1917 and has had
representative offices in Beijing, Shanghai and Guangzhou.
</P>
<P>
It jointly established the Allianz Dazhong Life Insurance
Company in Shanghai in 1998 with Shanghai's Dazhong Insurance
Company.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
