<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: Major Zones in Pudong (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai's Pudong New Area has
four major state-level zones with different development focuses,
namely, Lujiazui, Jinqiao, Waigaoqiao and Zhangjiang.
</P>
<P>
The 28-square-kilometer Lujiazui Finance and Trade Zone, along
the Huangpu River, has 83 financial facilities from both home and
abroad, including 42 foreign banks. Twenty-four of the foreign
banks have been licensed to engage in Renminbi business.
</P>
<P>
The zone is home to six state-level markets, approximately 200
skyscrapers, 103 Chinese foreign trade companies, and a sizable
exhibition hall. Lujiazui and the Bund on the western side of the
Huangpu River, are expected to form Shanghai's central business
district (CBD) in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Jinqiao Exports Processing Zone, covering an area of 20 square
kilometers, lies in the central part of Pudong. It is home to the
manufacturing industry, where joint ventures with General Motors,
Bell, Sharp and other multinationals are located. Some 340
projects have been launched there, more than 80 percent of which
are in the high-tech category. The high-tech projects are involved
in four major sectors including automobiles, electronic
information, modern electric household appliances and bio-medicine.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
