<HEADLINE> Farmers Looking for Jobs in West China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, April 18 (Xinhua) -- An increasing number of farmers
in east China's Jiangxi Province are moving to the western part of
China to make earnings.
</P>
<P>
For a long time, farmers would choose to work in economically-
advantaged coastal areas, but the trend has changed as China has
kicked off a national campaign to develop its western part.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that more than 30,000 Jiangxi people went to
western China in March, and 11,000 farmers were from Xingguo
County alone.
</P>
<P>
More than 200 technicians from Dingnan County, known as "China'
s Sweet Pear Town", plan to build pear gardens in Yunnan and
Sichuan provinces in southwest China.
</P>
<P>
Local sources said that more than 200 farmers in Jinxi County
have gone to some west Chinese towns to grow vegetables.
</P>
<P>
The provincial labor departments have offered formal and
regular service for the farmers. One example is that Xingguo
County established special files for the farmers and helped them
to find jobs in western China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
