<HEADLINE> Anhui Expands Economic Cooperation with Taiwan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Taiwan business people have
contracted to invest 710 million US dollars in east China's Anhui
Province by the end of 1999, according to sources from a local
symposium.
</P>
<P>
A total of 16 Taiwan-funded enterprises and some provincial
departments held a special symposium recently to discuss how to
protect the interests of Taiwan investors in Anhui in line with
concerned State regulations.
</P>
<P>
The Taiwan participants said that they have enhanced their
confidence in investing in Anhui, as the Chinese mainland has
provided better protection for their interests.
</P>
<P>
The province has approved 768 Taiwan-funded projects, with a
total investment of 962 million US dollars. Meanwhile, Anhui has
sent more than 20 groups to Taiwan at invitations to negotiate
trade cooperation, the sources said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
