<DOCNO> XIE20000418.0229 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia's First On-Line Stock Trading Launched </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 18 (Xinhua) -- In a bid to offer faster, more
efficient and more cost effective service to investors by tapping
the Internet, Indonesia's first on-line stock trading system was
launched here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The on-line trading, namely Makindo Cybertrade, was set up by
PT.MAKINDO, Indonesia's premier independent investment bank.
</P>
<P>
Makindo Cybertrade, with the best in secure e-Commerce
technology and commitment to excellence in customer service, will
provide convenience to retail investors while empowering them with
the information to make their own decision, the company's
President Director Gunawan Jusuf said at a press conference after
the launching ceremony.
</P>
<P>
He said subscribers of Makindo Cybertrade will receive a full
range of quality services including comprehensive stock market
information, new and real time stock quotes through the internet.
</P>
<P>
Subscribers will also be able to monitor their stock portfolio
by instructing Cybertrade to notify them of any pricing activities,
involving a list of stocks they are invested in. The system will
do this without any human intervention.
</P>
<P>
Gunawan said his company is aware the e-Commerce is still young
in Indonesia and for it to grow to its full potential, substantial
improvement to the country's information technology infrastructure
must be carried out. However, Makindo is convinced that it must be
the first investment bank in the country to be ready when the
market is ready. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
