<DOCNO> XIE20000418.0231 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Angolan Rate of Unemployment Estimated to Exceed 55% till 2001 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Unemployment rate in Angola is
estimated to exceed 55 percent in the year of 2001, mainly due to
the poor state of health and the level of the education system,
Angolan Minister of Education and Culture Burity da Silva said
here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
According to da Silva, the unemployment rate next year will
range between 55 percent and 65 percent in the war-torn southwest
African country. The minister predicted that it will have
negative consequences on the local level of production, and
clearly reflects the rate of poverty facing the Angolan people.
</P>
<P>
He said that if appropriate policies are not adopted, the high
unemployment rate might also result in a sick population,
unproductive industry and negative impact on the social-economic
development.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on the country's current context, the minister said
the efforts made by the experts of education and health are
hindered by the promoters of violence in its extreme form, namely
the armed conflicts. "Our efforts in preserving life are
continuously hindered by those who promote, in gratuitous and
criminal way, the loss of human lives", he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
