<DOCNO> XIE20000418.0233 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Mixed in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices closed mixed in Tokyo
Tuesday, with the benchmark Nikkei index ending below 19,000
despite Monday's sharp rebound on Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange closed below 19,000 for the
first time in 12 weeks, losing 39.12 points, or 0.21 percent from
Monday's close to 18,969.52.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index which covers all
First Section issues, however, rose 43.94 points or 2.83 percent
to 1,596.40.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section decreased to 749.15 million
shares from Monday's 875.11 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Steel maker NKK was the day's volume leader.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei hit the day's high of 19,330.40 just after opening
as investors welcomed the overnight gain in New York share prices,
traders said.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei, however, turned downward shortly as investors
heavily sold issues to be deleted from the key index's components
next Monday.
</P>
<P>
Helped by the gain on Wall Street and the U.S. dollar's rebound
to the mid-104 yen range, export-oriented high-tech blue chips
were higher, while information and technology issues also regained
upward momentum.
</P>
<P>
Brokerages, Monday's worst performers, drew active buying.
</P>
<P>
Retailers, banks and chemical firms were among gainers, while
wholesalers, warehousing firms and nonbank moneylenders saw
declines, traders said.
</P>
<P>
Of the issues listed on the First Section, gainers outpaced
losers 880 to 384, while 121 issues closed unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
