<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Investigates More Corruption Cases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese capital dealt with 80
cases concerning corruption in the first quarter this year, up 33
percent over the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman with the Beijing People's Procuratorate revealed at
today's press conference that officials responsible for bureaus or
section offices were named in 20 cases, and 59 were cases
involving over 50,000 yuan (about 6,000 US dollars) of palm grease,
an increase of 69 percent over last year.
</P>
<P>
He noted that 23 cases involved more than one million yuan (120,
000 US dollars) of illegal money, double last year's figure.
</P>
<P>
During 1998 and 1999, 2,362 cases of corruption were examined
by the Beijing procuratorate, with 77 cases involving more than
one million yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000418.0235 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Most Profitable Businesses In China: Economists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Chinese economists have predicted
nine most profitable businesses, most of which are related to the
commerce industry, in China in the future.
</P>
<P>
An analysis by local economists on the Beijing Economic Daily
quoted shows that sales of household electrical appliances will
enjoy a continuous boom under the sustained growth of China's
national economy. The returns of the investment in this sector
will reach 10-35 percent.
</P>
<P>
Telecommunications sector will be one of the largest business
in China because of its great potential market. At present, the
availability of phones to Chinese citizens now stands at a meagre
four percent, much lower than the world average of 10 percent.
</P>
<P>
House interior decoration is expected to undergo a faster
development as more and more people are expected to spend more
money in this consumption area. The house interior decoration
expenditure per household is 20,000 yuan (about 2,410 US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The real estate sector will be more prosperous as individual
purchase of housing will account for the bulk of the market. Also,
sales agents and consultants are believed to be well-paid.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, with more private cars going into homes of
ordinary citizens, related businesses such as car maintenance and
car washing will also be boosted.
</P>
<P>
Other profitable businesses include tourism, fast-food industry,
and products for the elderly and women. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000418.0236 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Top Two Container Ports Perform Well </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The handling capacity of China's
two largest container ports -- Shanghai and Shenzhen -- increased
greatly in the first quarter this year.
</P>
<P>
That of Shanghai reached 1.18 million TEUs, an increase of 34
percent on a year-on-year basis, according to related statistics.
</P>
<P>
The container port's handling capacity in March hit a record
volume of 430,000 TEUs, 110,000 TEUs more than that in the same
period of 1999.
</P>
<P>
During the first quarter this year, Shenzhen reached 816,000
TEUs, a rise of 43.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
The gross cargo handling capacity of the two ports stood at 48.
6 million tons and 12.06 million tons, respectively.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the container transferring volume of Shanghai in
the first quarter also increased by 60 percent over the same
period of last year, thanks to the port's efforts to expand its
transport volume inside the Yangtze River navigation system.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
