<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Release Monthly Economic Figures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Beginning this month, China will
release its latest economic statistics on a monthly basis.
</P>
<P>
The National Bureau of Statistics (NBS) announced today at a
press conference sponsored by the Information Office under the
State Council that it will issue the first monthly publication of
China Monthly Economic Indicators in late April.
</P>
<P>
The monthly will be published in both English and Chinese, and
will contain the latest figures on investment, the budget, prices,
finance, trade, real estate, and other aspects of the economy.
</P>
<P>
Along with macroeconomic and microeconomic indicators, the
monthly publication will also include economic forecasts. 
</P>
