<HEADLINE> Sixth China-ASEAN Senior Officials Meeting to Be Held in Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua)-- The sixth China-ASEAN Senior
Officials Meeting (SOM) will be held at Kuching of Malaysia from
April 25 to 26, according to Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman
Sun Yuxi.
</P>
<P>
Sun made the announcement here this afternoon at the regular
press conference.
</P>
<P>
He said that Chinese Vice Foreign Minister Yang Wenchang will
co-chair the meeting with Abdul Kadir Mohamad, secretary general
of Foreign Ministry of Malaysia, the coordinating country of the
sixth SOM.
</P>
<P>
Sun added that the vice foreign ministers of Cambodia,
Indonesia, the Laos, Myanmar, the Philippines, Thailand, Viet Nam,
permanent secretaries of Brunei and Singapore, and officials of
the ASEAN Secretariat will attend the meeting.
</P>
<P>
He noted that since 1995, the China-ASEAN SOM has been held
five times, playing a positive role in deepening cooperation in
all fields and establishing good neighborly partnership of mutual
confidence between China and the ASEAN. 
