<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Farmer Jailed for Selling Golden Monkey Skin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- A farmer in northwest China's
Shaanxi Province is now serving a three-year jail term for
illegally selling the skin of a state-protected golden monkey,
according to a report in the latest China Environment News.
</P>
<P>
Kang Xiangjun, a farmer in Taibai County of Shaanxi Province,
was convicted earlier this year by a local court of skinning a
golden monkey he found in a hill near his home last year and
attempting to sell, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
The court, the People's Court of Taibai County, also ordered
Kang to pay a fine of 4,000 yuan (about 500 U.S. dollars) for the
attempted sale, which is banned under China's wildlife protection
laws.
</P>
<P>
The golden monkey is an endangered species at the top of China'
s state protection list. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
