<DOCNO> XIE20000418.0245 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Gamma Ray Medical Facility Developed in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua ) -- A new medical facility using
Gamma rays to treat tumors has been developed in China, the
Economic Information Daily reported today.
</P>
<P>
The national newspaper said the facility, the first large-scale
medical technology developed in China, was made by Shenzhen OUR
International Science &AMP; Technology Co. in cooperation with the
Hubei Machine Tool Plant and two universities.
</P>
<P>
Compared with traditional medical facilities using Gamma rays
to treat brain tumors, this new facility can be used to treat
tumors anywhere in the body, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The new facility, called the dimensional and directional Gamma
ray treatment system, has been registered with the State Drug
Administration, according to the newspaper. 
</P>
</TEXT>
