<HEADLINE> N. Zealand Tells UN of Concern Over Sanctions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The United Nations Security Council needs to give priority to "
a more focused and refined approach to sanctions to reduce
humanitarian suffering", the minister said in the statement.
</P>
<P>
The New Zealand move coincides with an open debate on general
issues relating to sanctions in the Security Council Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Goff noted that comprehensive sanctions were a "blunt
instrument"and could cause "devastating suffering and long-term
degradation to civilian populations, far in excess of the damages
inflicted by armed conflict and war."
</P>
<P>
He recommended that the Security Council focus on "designing
better targeted sanction regimes with clear objectives and exit
strategies,regular reviews and stronger institutional support".
</P>
