<HEADLINE> Lusaka Hotels Fully Booked by Eclipse Enthusiasts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Almost all the hotels in Zambian
capital Lusaka have been fully booked by eclipse enthusiasts as
the lunar eclipse will pass through Zambia on June 21, 2001.
</P>
<P>
"Almost all hotels and lodges in Lusaka are fully booked by
eclipse enthusiasts from various parts of the world," Zambia Daily
Mail Tuesday quoted marketing manager of the Zambia National
Tourists Board (ZNTB), Cletus Chanda, as saying.
</P>
<P>
He said ZNTB will ensure that transport, accommodation, and
other facilities will be adequately provided for the enthusiasts.
</P>
<P>
ZNTB has intensified its tourism marketing strategies in the
country, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said the intensification of the marketing strategies is
going on well and the response from both local and international
markets is overwhelming.
</P>
<P>
The lunar eclipse will increase tourism arrivals and revenues
in the country, Chanda said. 
</P>
