<HEADLINE> East African Soldiers to Hold Military Exercise in Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Some 4,000 troops from three east
African countries and the United States will converge at the
Kenyan coast this weekend for a military exercise, the East
African Standard newspaper reported on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Large military trucks from Uganda are currently running on the
Mombasa- Nairobi highway ferrying soldiers in preparation of the
massive exercise, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Bogita Ongeri, public relation officer at Kenya's Department of
Defense, said soldiers from Kenya, Uganda, Tanzania and the United
States will participate in a joint training session dubbed Natural
Fire 2000.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,000 American troops are expected to arrive this
week, Ongeri said, adding that Uganda and Tanzania will contribute
300 troops each, while Kenya will contribute 2,000 soldiers, for
the exercise.
</P>
<P>
The multi-national exercise is aimed at training east African
soldiers for peacekeeping missions, Ongeri said. 
</P>
