<DOCNO> XIE20000418.0263 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, France to Set Up Tap Water Plant at Yellow River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, April 18 (Xinhua) -- China plans to set up a tap
water plant with advanced technology on the banks of the Yellow
River in Zhengzhou, capital of central China's Henan province, in
collaboration with France.
</P>
<P>
Each side will hold 50 percent of the cooperative project, and
Jacques Letondot, managing director of the Suez Lyonnaise Des Eaux
of France, said that they are quite optimistic about the 30-year
contract.
</P>
<P>
Zhengzhou officials said tap water plant, with an investment of
37.8 million U.S. dollars, will not discharge any waste water,
residue, or gas, and will use hi-tech French equipment.
</P>
<P>
Experts say the project is expected to have a positive
influence on pollution control and water and soil erosion along
the Yellow River.
</P>
<P>
Half of the ten provinces included in the plan to develop
western China are located at the upper or middle reaches of the
Yellow River. 
</P>
</TEXT>
