<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nothing Unusual in Breakup of South Pole Icebergs: Expert </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese South Pole expert has
described the recent breakup of three huge icebergs at the South
Pole as nothing unusual.
</P>
<P>
Xie Simei, a member of China's 14th South Pole Expedition Team,
told reporters today that icebergs at the South and North Poles
break up every year, especially in summer when drifting icebergs
are easily seen via satellite images.
</P>
<P>
Icebergs covering a total of 3,000 sq.km. melted last year,
said Xie, who is also head of the Polar Region Forecast Group
under the State Maritime Administration.
</P>
<P>
Reports of the three huge icebergs that broke up and have been
drifting for the past month have caused concern over their effect
on the global climate, as one of the icebergs is about 10 times
the size of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Xie said the breakup was not the result of global warming as
many people believe, arguing that gravitation, warm weather, and
tidal activity are the causes of the phenomenon.
</P>
<P>
The Antarctic is covered by ice and snow as thick as 2,000
meters, and icecaps on the brim of the continent can easily break
up piece by piece and slip into the sea due to the temperature and
tidal effects, he explained.
</P>
<P>
The continent loses some icebergs, but gains in snowfall each
year to maintain the balance, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000418.0265 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Should Improve Chip Designing Capability: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- China should expand the
application of integrated circuitry as a first step in the
development of the chip designing industry, a seminar was told in
Shanghai Monday.
</P>
<P>
Hui Yongzheng, vice-minister of Science and Technology, told a
seminar on development of the micro-electronics industry in China
that the country must become able to develop chips on its own for
application in national defense, national security, and key
economic sectors, according to Monday's Shanghai-based Wenhui
Daily.
</P>
<P>
By the year 2005, at least 40 percent of the chips for these
sectors should be locally produced, while 30 percent of the chips
for integrated circuits, consumer goods, and telecommunications
should be locally designed and produced, the vice-minister said.
</P>
<P>
The seminar was sponsored by the Ministry of Science and
Technology. 
</P>
</TEXT>
