<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Magic Stopped from Eastern Playoffs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The Orlando Magic was deprived
of their final playoff spot as they were beaten at home by the
Milwaukee Bucks 85-83 on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Magic once rallied from a 19-point deficit and led with 1:
17 left before Glenn Robinson converted a breakaway layup with 14.
8 seconds left.
</P>
<P>
After Robinson's basket, Orlando went for the win but Chucky
Atkins missed a 3-pointer from the right corner with five seconds
remaining. Robinson slapped the rebound into the backcourt and
time ran out.
</P>
<P>
Milwaukee (41-40) completed a four-game season sweep of the
Magic and is one-half game behind seventh-place Detroit in the
East.
</P>
<P>
In Philadelphia, the Indiana Pacers fought back from a 10-point
deficit to defeat the 76ers 92-90, ending the 76ers' hopes of
catching the New York Knicks for third place in the Eastern
Conference.
</P>
<P>
Allen Iverson led Philadelphia with 24 points.
</P>
<P>
In San Antonio, David Robinson scored 12 of his 27 points in
the fourth quarter, helping the Spurs rally from a 12-point
deficit to defeat the Vancouver Grizzlies 100-93, keeping alive
their hopes of gaining home-court advantage in the first round of
the playoffs.
</P>
<P>
Tim Duncan sat out his third straight game with torn cartilage
in his left knee.
</P>
<P>
At Golden State, the Minnesota Timberwolves beat the Warriors
101-96. 
</P>
</TEXT>
