<HEADLINE> Security Center to Operate for ADB Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The Thai Interior Ministry will
set up a center to handle security for the May 6-8 annual meeting
of the Asian Development Bank in Chiang Mai, a northern city of
Thailand, the Bangkok Post reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper quoted a source as saying that the center will
operate from May 2-9. It will be assisted by the Thai National
Intelligence Agency, the Thai National Security Center, the Thai
Armed Forces Security Center, The Special Branch Police, the Thai
National Police Office and the Local Administration Department.
</P>
<P>
It is expected that during the meeting, local and foreign
activist groups will raise environmental and other concerns.
</P>
<P>
The interior ministry will assign a six-man intelligence team
to Chiang Mai from May 1 to monitor movements of such activist
groups until the close of the ADB conference.
</P>
<P>
All provincial governors have also been instructed to step up
security measures, especially for public utilities, in their areas
of jurisdiction.
</P>
<P>
Some 3,200 delegates from 58 countries are expected to attend
the ADB meeting in Chiang Mai. 
</P>
</TEXT>
