and Seoul should send their five-member negotiation teams led by a
vice minister to attend the preparatory meetings.
</P>
<P>
In early April this year, South Korea and the DPRK reached an
agreement in China, under which South Korean President Kim Dae-
jung will travel to Pyongyang for a summit with DPRK leader Kim
Jong-il.
</P>
<P>
It will be the first-ever inter-Korean summit since the Korean
War in the early 1950s. 
