<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Documentary on Late Communist Leader in Making </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- China has started shooting a ten-
part documentary on Qu Qiubai (1899-1935), one of the major
leaders of the Communist Party of China (CPC) in its early years,
in this capital of east China's Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
The documentary will focus on Qu's studying experience in
Russia, his activities in 1927 at the post of general secretary of
the party, and his great contribution to literature in China.
</P>
<P>
Qu, a native of Changzhou in Jiangsu Province, was an
outstanding proletarian revolutionary and theorist.
</P>
<P>
On June 18, 1935, Qu Qiubai was executed by Kuomintang
reactionaries in Changding County in east China's Fujian Province.
</P>
<P>
The film is jointly produced by the Party Literature Research
Center of the CPC Central Committee and the Jiangsu Provincial
Society of Qu Qiubai Studies.  
</P>
</TEXT>
