<HEADLINE> China Expects Faster Economic Growth This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- China's steady economic growth in
the first quarter showed signs of a better future, and the growth
of gross domestic product(GDP) this year is expected to surpass
that of last year, the National Bureau of Statistics said today.
</P>
<P>
Liu Chengxiang, spokesman for the bureau, said at a press
conference here that this year's economic growth rate will be a
little higher than 1999 given that all the fiscal policies are
well implemented.
</P>
