<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Industrial Production Maintains Fast Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- China's industry maintained a
fast-growing pace in the first quarter of this year with added
values totaling 501.2 billion yuan, or a rise of 10.7 percent as
compared with the same period last year, the National Bureau of
Statistics said here today.
</P>
<P>
The figure represented an increase of 3.4 percentage points as
compared with the fourth quarter of 1999.
</P>
<P>
The country witnessed an increase of 8.6 percent in the state-
owned or state-holding enterprises, a 7.7 percent rise in the
collectively-owned enterprises and a 14.4 percent rise in the
foreign-funded enterprises.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the country's heavy industry achieved an increase
of 11.5 percent in the first quarter, showing 1.7 percent faster
than the light industry.
</P>
<P>
And telecom products and equipment, electronic computers, micro
computers and integrated circuit products showed increases ranging
between 16.3 and 73.1 percent. The mobile phones showed a 1.4-fold
increase.
</P>
<P>
The industrial production and marketing rate in the first
quarter stood at 95.92 percent. And the comprehensive index of
industrial enterprises in the first two months stood at 95.83,
showing a rise of 15.6 percentage points as compared with same
period of last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
