<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Forecasts Moderate Rebound of Prices </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- China's falling consumer prices
have picked up in the first quarter and will keep the growing
momentum this year, but at a moderate pace, said Liu Cheng Xiang,
spokesman for the National Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
Liu, speaking at a news conference here today, attributed the
rebound of prices to the stimulated demand as well as to the
seasonal factors, mainly spending spree in the lunar new year
holidays during the past months.
</P>
<P>
The consumer prices in China edged up 0.7 percent on an annual
basis in February after declining for a consecutive 22 months.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
