<HEADLINE> China Sees Improved Agricultural Mix </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- China's grain-growing fields will
be cut by 1.2 percent this year as against 1999, but high-quality
rice will increase by 1.6 percent, the National Bureau of
Statistics said today.
</P>
<P>
Total crop-growing area will increase by 400,000 hectares to
reach 156 million hectares this year, said Liu Chengxiang,
spokesman for the bureau.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, sown areas for sugar and cotton will be
reduced amidst growth in edible oil and vegetables. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
