<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hungary's Budget Deficit Sharply Drops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Hungary has achieved a balanced
budget with a sharp reduction in state deficit for the first
quater of this year, said the Central Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest figure released by the bureau,
Hungary's budget deficit for the first quater this year dropped by
49.3 percent to 153.4 billion forint (572.4 million U.S. dollars),
compared with the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The country's budget deficit for 1999 was 441 billion forint (1.
66 billion dollars), 0.7 percentage point down from 1998's level
and 17 billion forint (63.4 million dollars) less than the planned
figure.
</P>
<P>
This year the deficit is estimated at 435.8 billion forint (1.
63 billion dollars), accounting for 3.5 percent of gross domestic
product.
</P>
<P>
However, experts warned that expenditures on agriculture in the
first three months have reached 137 billion forint (511.2 million
dollars), or 41.5 percent of the whole year's level, which is
likely to leave a negative impact on the implementation of this
year's budget plan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
