<HEADLINE> Shaanxi To Support 20 Key High-tech Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Shaanxi province in northwest China
has decided to give special support to 20 selected high-tech
projects, local government officials said today.
</P>
<P>
The 20 projects for commercialization of research findings will
enjoy more preferential treatment than projects that involve
conventional technologies.
</P>
<P>
The move is aimed at fostering in three years 10 successful
high-tech enterprises each with annual sales exceeding 1 billion
yuan (120 million U.S. dollars), they added.
</P>
<P>
The selected high-tech projects have stronger competitive edge
and huge market potential, and they involve information technology,
home electric appliances, environmental protection, software
development, pharmaceuticals and medical equipment.
</P>
<P>
Despite its strong strength of science and technology, Shaanxi
has been slow in commercializing many high-tech findings, thus
hindering local economic development, the officials noted.
</P>
<P>
The local government has invited 20 high-tech firms to
undertake the projects, they said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
