<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Forage from Yellow River Delta to Be Exported to Canada </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The Yellow River Delta, east China'
s Shandong Province, is expected to turn out 2 million kilograms
of forage for export to Canada this year.
</P>
<P>
Xinhua has learned that a Canadian-funded enterprise has
established a forage producing base in the delta area and has
signed contracts with local producers for purchasing the fodder.
</P>
<P>
The Yellow River Delta covers 8,000-sq km area around the mouth
of the river, which is to the east of Lijin County of Shandong
Province.
</P>
<P>
The region boasts suitable weather, ample sunshine and little
pollution, making it an ideal place to grow fodder. A 666.66-ha
area in the delta has been opened up for planting quality grasses
such as purple medic.
</P>
<P>
The local producers have imported equipment for harvesting,
bundling and drying grasses to improve product quality.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
