<DOCNO> XIE20000418.0310 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Interbank Trading Up In First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Turnover on China's interbank
money market totaled 288.2 billion yuan during the first quarter
of this year, or about 4.648 billion yuan averaged for each of the
62 trading days, a 26.11 percent rise compared to the fourth
quarter of last year.
</P>
<P>
The total included 88.934 billion yuan in credit, 190.44
billion yuan in bond repurchase agreements, and 8.821 billion yuan
in spot bonds.
</P>
<P>
The weighted average interbank lending rate and repurchasing
rate were 2.53 percent and 2.51 percent respectively during the
first quarter, with both showing a slight downward trend. 
</P>
</TEXT>
