<HEADLINE> Myanmar's Cement Output Drops in 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar produced a total of 338,
007 tons of cement in 1999, a drop of 7.38 percent compared with
1998, according to the latest figures published by the country's
Central Statistical Organization.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, Myanmar has sped up the pace of
infrastructural construction of roads, bridges and dams, resulting
in a shortage of cement day by day.
</P>
<P>
To meet the rising demand for cement, the Myanmar government
spends large sums of foreign exchange importing cement annually
while planning to build more cement plants.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar is reportedly trying to get a foreign loan of 150
million U.S. dollars to build a 4,000-ton daily-capacity cement
plant. 
</P>
