<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xinjiang Expands Cotton Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Cotton has become the number one
export commodity in northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous
Region, replacing garments and accessories.
</P>
<P>
According to figures released by the local Customs, the region
exported 40,000 tons of cotton at more than 42 million U.S.
dollars in January and February, an increase of 15 times year-on-
year and accounting for one third of the region's total exports in
the period.
</P>
<P>
Xinjiang is the largest cotton producer in China. Last year,
the region produced 135,000 tons of cotton, about one third of the
country's total cotton output.
</P>
<P>
Local trade officials attributed the rise in cotton exports to
a reform in the cotton distribution system, adjusted pricing in
line with international markets, and improvements in cotton
quality.
</P>
<P>
In the first two months, Xinjiang exported to Indonesia 12,600
tons of cotton worth of over 13 million dollars, to the Republic
of Korea 11,200 tons worth of some 12 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Thailand and Malaysia were also big importers of Xinjiang
cotton.
</P>
<P>
The rise in cotton exports not only greatly reduced cotton
inventories, but also increased the income of local farmers, gave
a boost to Xinjiang's economy and helped the restructuring of
local textile industry, local trade officials said.
</P>
<P>
At present, Xinjiang exported its cotton mainly to Southeast
Asian nations, but it is also trying to tap new markets in Latin
America and Africa.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
