<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Direct Cross-Straits Shipping Hits New High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The volume of cargo shipped
directly between Xiamen in Fujian Province and Kaohsiung in Taiwan
hit a record high of 95,321 TEUs of containers during the first
quarter this year, a 28.3 percent rise on a yearly basis.
</P>
<P>
This volume accounted for 76.5 percent of the total cargo
transported directly between the two sides of the Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
The Xiamen port handled 243,957 TEUs of containers during the
first quarter of the year, up 30.2 percent over the 1999 figure.
</P>
<P>
Xiamen has now opened nine overseas routes linked to Europe,
America, Japan, Singapore, and the ROK, as well as Hong Kong and
Taiwan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
