<HEADLINE> Chinese Customs Find Mediterranean Fruit Flies From America </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The Guangzhou Entry-Exit
Inspection and Quarantine Bureau said that it had found
Mediterranean Fruit Flies in fruit boxes imported from the U.S.
</P>
<P>
The Jiulong Paper Industry Co. Ltd. imported 101 containers of
paper to wrap fruit from Long Beach, America. Quarantine
inspectors found the fruit flies in the shipment and have ordered
the goods to be sealed and fumigated.
</P>
<P>
The full-grown Mediterranean Fruit Fly is only one cm long. It
has high reproductive rate and can breed 200 million eggs within
60 days.  
</P>
</TEXT>
