<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cyprus Can Join EU Without Solution of Political Issue: EU Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus can join the European Union
(EU) without a prior solution of its political issue, European
Parliament member Mechtild Rhote said here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Rhote and Cypriot legislator Tassos Papadopoulos, co-
chairpersons of the 17th meeting of the Joint EU-Cyprus
Parliamentary Committee opening here Monday, told reporters that
Turkey cannot begin EU accession talks unless it withdraws its
troops from northern Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
The EU Helsinki summit last December dispersed any ideas that
Turkey could obstruct Cyprus' EU accession, Rhote said.
</P>
<P>
She ruled out the possibility of separate negotiations with the
Turkish Cypriot side, whose breakaway regime in northern Cyprus was
recognized only by Ankara.
</P>
<P>
She expressed regret at the Turkish Cypriots' refusal to join
the Cyprus team by nominating their representatives in the
negotiations for Cyprus' EU entry.
</P>
<P>
"We want something concrete in the Cyprus question," Rhote said,
expressing the view that the situation as far as the Cyprus issue
is concerned has improved somewhat after the December EU summit in
Helsinki.
</P>
<P>
"It is in Turkey's interest to join the EU but Ankara must put
an end to its occupation of Cyprus' northern part as negotiations
cannot start until the troops withdraw and human rights in Turkey
are respected," Rhote said.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus has been divided into the Greek Cypriot-controlled south
and Turkish Cypriots-dominated north since 1974 when Turkey invaded
and occupied the northern third of the island in reaction to a pro-
Athens coup in Nicosia.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus applied for EU membership in 1990 and started substantive
accession negotiations with the EU in November 1998.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish Cypriot side has so far turned down an invitation by
President Glafcos Clerides to nominate representatives in the
official team negotiating the republic's EU accession.
</P>
<P>
In his remarks, Papadopoulos called on Turkey to comply with the
provisions of the Helsinki decisions, if it wants to start EU
accession negotiations.
</P>
<P>
The Joint EU-Cyprus Parliamentary Committee meeting takes place
every six months to review Cyprus' ties with the EU. The two-day
17th joint meeting started Monday. The next meeting will be held in
Brussels in October. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
