<HEADLINE> Romania, Arab League Share Views on Mideast Peace: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Romania has identical views with the
Arab League on the importance of realizing a just and comprehensive
peace in the Middle East, the visiting Romanian Foreign Minister
Petre Roman said here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Roman told reporters after meeting Arab League Secretary General
Esmat Abdel-Meguid that they discussed the latest developments of
the Arab-Israeli peace talks on the Palestinian, Syrian and
Lebanese tracks.
</P>
<P>
Roman, who arrived here on Monday for a three-day visit to
Egypt, urged the parties to exert more efforts to achieve a just
and comprehensive peace for regional development and prosperity.
</P>
<P>
The talks also covered the possibility that the pan-Arab forum
takes part in the partnership dialog with the Organization of
Security and Cooperation in Europe (OSCE), he said, stressing that
five countries on the eastern and southern Mediterranean coast have
participated in the process.
</P>
<P>
An OSCE-Arab partnership will help realize peace and stability
in both regions, he said. 
</P>
