<HEADLINE> Clashes Erupt Among Palestinian Students in Gaza </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GAZA, April 18 (Xinhua) -- About 35 people including six
policemen were injured in bloody confrontations between two groups
of students from the Islamic University and Azhar University in
Gaza on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The confrontations started in the Hamas-dominated Islamic
University when supporters of Hamas tried to prevent some of
followers of Fatah, the mainstay of the Palestine Liberation
Organization, from sticking photos of Palestinian leader Yasser
Arafat and Fatah leader Khalil al-Wazir, according to Palestinian
sources.
</P>
<P>
The situation worsened when some students from the Fatah-
dominated Azhar University got involved in the clashes. The two
groups of students threw stones at each other and some of them
sustained injuries as a result.
</P>
<P>
All of the injured were hospitalized and some of them left the
hospital after being treated, Director of the Palestinian Police
General Ghazi al-Jibali said.
</P>
<P>
After the clashes broke out, the two universities' boards asked
the police to get into the two university campuses to restore
security and tranquility, according to Jibali.
</P>
<P>
Around 350 policemen riding in 50 vehicles rushed to the scene
to disperse the students.
</P>
<P>
The two universities have been sealed off to facilitate the
investigation into the bloody incident.
</P>
<P>
It was alleged that the clashes erupted partly due to the Hamas
students' anger over their defeat in the latest student elections.
</P>
<P>
However, Jibali said the Hamas students won the election of the
Islamic University with a 75 percent majority. The election of
Azhar University will be held next week, he noted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
