<HEADLINE> Nigeria to Host African Summit to Fight Malaria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Most of the deaths are in Africa which faces climate changes,
population movement arising from political instability and civil
strife, resistance of mosquitoes to insecticides and poor national
health services.
</P>
<P>
One of the agencies, the United Nations Development Program (
UNDP) has recommended low-cost mosquito nets, potent and
inexpensive medicines, and timely and accurate information about
malaria as measures to prevent malaria from spreading. 
</P>
