<HEADLINE> FAO Calls for Urgent Food Aid to Horn of Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In a special alert issued from Rome and through U.N.
headquarters in New York, the FAO said speedier delivery of food
aid is required to avoid further human suffering and loss of life.
</P>
<P>
In addition to Ethiopia where more than 8 million people are
facing severe food shortages, food crisis is also affecting
Burundi, Djibouti, Kenya, Rwanda, Somalia, Sudan, Uganda and
Tanzania, the U.N. agency said.
</P>
<P>
It put food aid requirements for the region at about 2 million
tonnes, more than double last year's volume and the highest level
for the past 15 years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
