<HEADLINE> Canada, Greenland to Establish Maritime Link </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Canada's Quebec Transport
Desgagnes Inc. Tuesday announced an agreement with a Denmark-
Greenland company on the establishment of the first-ever direct
maritime link between Canada and Greenland.
</P>
<P>
Under the deal, Transport Desgagnes Inc. will be offering
container and other cargo service between Montreal and Nuuk on
behalf of Royal Arctic Line, an ocean carrier operating between
Denmark and Greenland.
</P>
<P>
The first voyage will be in July and one or two other trips can
be added in summer if trade grows rapidly between Canada and
Greenland,according to the agreement.
</P>
<P>
Royal Arctic Line was seeking a Canadian partner in a bid to
open up the North American market to Greenlanders, the Canadian
company said.
</P>
<P>
Transport Desgagnes Inc. was chosen because of its expertise
and experience in navigating the Arctic waters of eastern Canada,
said the Canadian company.
</P>
<P>
Royal Arctic Line runs a modern fleet offering regular service
between the Danish port of Aalborg and 13 ports in Greenland.
</P>
</TEXT>
