<HEADLINE> China, Netherlands to Increase Exchanges Between Parliaments </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
THE HAGUE (The Netherlands), April 18 (Xinhua) -- China and the
Netherlands agreed here on Tuesday that exchanges between the
legislatures of the two countries should be further promoted so as
to help push forward the overall cooperation between the two
nations.
</P>
<P>
The agreement came at the meeting here between visiting Chinese
Vice Premier Li Lanqing and the Dutch parliament leaders, Speaker
of the Second Chamber Mrs. Jeltje van Nieuwenhoven and Speaker of
the First Chamber Mr. Korthals Altes.
</P>
<P>
The Dutch parliament leaders welcomed Li's current visit to the
Netherlands, which started on Sunday, and expressed their desire
for further promoting exchanges between the two countries in all
fields,including that of the legislative bodies, so as to enhance
mutual understanding and expand bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Li said he believed that the continuous development of
exchanges and cooperation between the People's Congress of China (
the parliament) and the Dutch parliament will surely become a
sustained and important driving force for the development of the
friendly cooperation of mutual benefit between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Before the meeting, Li was present at a signing ceremony of a
memorandum of understanding between China and the Netherlands on
future cooperation in the fields of education and science and
technology.
</P>
<P>
Li was here on a three-day official visit, the third leg of his
four-nation trip to Latin America and Europe. 
</P>
</TEXT>
