<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Enhanced Cooperation Between Chinese, Dutch SMEs Called For </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMSTERDAM (The Netherlands), April 18 (Xinhua) -- Visiting
Chinese Vice Premier Li Lanqing called on the small and medium-
sized enterprises (SMEs) of China and the Netherlands to expand
their cooperation areas and enhance the level of their existing
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to a group of prominent Dutch businessmen, Li said the
Chinese and Dutch economies are highly complimentary to each other
in their development, and there is a great potential for further
cooperation as China is giving priority to the development of such
sectors of energy industry, electronics industry, chemical
industry and agriculture.
</P>
<P>
As China's development is offering new opportunities for
foreign businessmen, Li said he hoped the business circles of the
two countries would increase exchanges between them and try to
explore new areas of cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He noted that in the process of development, the Chinese SMEs
need foreign investment, advanced technology and experience of
management,which are exactly what the Dutch SMEs have to offer.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government will continue to support the cooperation
between the SMEs of the two countries, the Vice Premier said.
</P>
<P>
He also called on the Dutch SMEs to actively participate in
China's drive to develop the inner and western parts of the
country, which, as he stressed, promises great business
opportunities for foreign enterprises. 
</P>
</TEXT>
