<HEADLINE> U.S. Tour Helicopter Crashes At Grand Canyon Inside Arizona </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The tour helicopter crashed shortly after taking off south of
Grand Canyon National Park, said Coconino County Sheriff's Sgt.
Randy Servis.
</P>
<P>
The helicopter crashed in windy conditions, but it was not
known if the crash was weather related, he added.
</P>
<P>
Helicopter tours of the canyon are a popular tourist attraction.
</P>
<P>
Servis said the seven people had been taken to two local
hospitals, but their injuries were not life threatening.
</P>
<P>
Tom Forman, a sheriff's spokesman, said Federal Aviation
Administration investigators were at the scene and the National
Transportation Safety Board was on its way to the site.
</P>
<P>
Snow and icy rain in the area caused several road accidents and
another aircraft was forced to make an emergency landing at nearby
Tuba City airport, Servis said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
