<HEADLINE> British Playwriter Slams U.S. for Hypocritical Civilized Values </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ATHENS, April 18 (Xinhua) -- British playwriter Harold Pinter
Tuesday criticized the U.S. for its hypocritical civilized values.
</P>
<P>
Addressing an audience at the Aristotelion University in the
northern Greek city of Thessaloniki, where he was awarded an
honorary doctorate of Philosophy, Pinter said that the term "
civilized values"in the U.S. sounded like a joke.
</P>
<P>
"Mr. Bill Clinton proclaims that the U.S. gave freedom to the
world. The U.S., in what values of our civilization do they
believe in? In a country with two million people in prison, in a
country where in prisons for juveniles children are incarcerated,
where guns are used, where torture is committed by remote control,
in a country where in 38 of its states the death penalty is still
in effect", he stated.
</P>
<P>
As for the danger of nuclear disaster, the renowned playwriter
said that the danger of nuclear disaster would not arise from the
"dangerous states" as the U.S. claims, but from the U.S. itself.
</P>
<P>
Pinter stressed that the U.S. proclaimed unabashedly that they
protected their interests through the use of military forces,
whenever and wherever was needed and the government of Britain
followed with an eagerness that deserves their disgust.
</P>
<P>
He also denounced NATO's military involvement in Yugoslavia
and criticized the British government for its policy.
</P>
<P>
"I feel ashamed of my country. Other countries also
participate in NATO but only the British government bent over and
kissed Clinton's feet," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
