<HEADLINE> Brazil, US Sign Space Accord </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The document is entitled "Accord on Safeguard Techniques
Related to the Participation of United States in Launchings from
Alcantara Launching Center".
</P>
<P>
Brazil's Minister of Science and Technology, Ronaldo Sardenberg,
and American ambassador, Anthony Harrington, signed the accord.
</P>
<P>
According to ALC authorities, this site has a capacity for 14
launchings per year.
</P>
<P>
From year 2001 to 2005 it is planned to send into space, from
ALC, 60 American satellites, which will be put into orbit by a
consortium made up by Ukraine and Italy.
</P>
<P>
Sources from Ministry of Science and Technology indicated the
commercial launching of foreign rockets will allow a widening and
modernizing of ALC's infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
The commercial operation of this center is expected to create 2,
500 jobs in Maranhao, where ALC is situated. 
</P>
</TEXT>
