<HEADLINE> Italy's Lazio Eliminated From Champions League Quarter Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Italian soccer team Lazio won Spain'
s Valencia 1-0 Tuesday night in the European Champions League
quarter-final's second leg, but eliminated 3-5 on aggregate.
</P>
<P>
Valencia had won Lazio 5-2 in first leg of quater-final.
</P>
<P>
Lazio's hope-giving goal came from a terrific 20-yard shot by
Argentinean play-maker Juan Sebastian Veron early in the second
half.
</P>
<P>
The Romans threw themselves forward with new heart but despite
several good chances - and a couple of tremendous saves by the
Valencia goalie - they were constantly frustrated.
</P>
<P>
Valencia had a few chances of their own, and had a goal
disallowed for offside with twenty minutes to go. 
</P>
</TEXT>
